Class SimpleSequence<T>

Direct Known Subclasses:
ArithmeticProgression, ConstantSequence, GeometricProgression
public abstract class SimpleSequence<T>
extends Sequence<T>
This is for special implementations for well-known sequences, such as geometric and arithmetic. It is useful to have a visitor because it allows us to compare two such objects, because otherwise a plain Sequence is not a data class and is not easy to compare given the interface that allows it to be return values for arbitrary numeric indices.
